text: Kõrb in 2011 Kaie Kõrb (born 1 April 1961 in Pärnu) is an Estonian ballet dancer and dance teacher. In 2006 she was described as "perhaps the country's most famous dancer today". She graduated from the Tallinn Ballet School (Tallinna Balletikool) in 1980, and was prima ballerina of the Estonian National Opera. She is now director of the Tallinn Ballet School. ==References== ==External links== *1985 photograph, performing Lazarev's Master and Margarita Category:1961 births Category:Living people Category:Estonian ballet dancers Category:Estonian female dancers Category:Recipients of the Order of the White Star, 3rd Class Category:People from Pärnu
